                  <tr>
                    <td valign="top" class="terms style1">1.</td>
                    <td valign="top" class="terms" style="font-size:12px;color:#666666;"><strong>Definitions</strong></td>
                  </tr>
                  <tr>
                    <td valign="top" class="terms style1">1.1</td>
                    <td valign="top" class="terms">&ldquo;Company&rdquo; shall mean The Tile Mob Pty Ltd its successors and assigns or any person acting on behalf of and with the authority of The Tile Mob Pty Ltd.</td>
                  </tr>
                  <tr>
                    <td valign="top" class="terms style1">1.2</td>
                    <td valign="top" class="terms">Customer&rdquo; shall mean the Customer (or any person acting on behalf of and with the authority of the Customer) as described on any quotation, work authorisation, invoice, sales order, order confirmation, tile enquiry, tile estimate, authority to hire or other form as provided by the Company to the Customer.</td>
                  </tr>
                  <tr>
                    <td valign="top" class="terms style1">1.3</td>
                    <td valign="top" class="terms">Guarantor&rdquo; means that person (or persons), or entity, who agrees to be liable for the debts of the Customer on a principal debtor basis.</td>
                  </tr>
                  <tr>
                    <td valign="top" class="terms style1">1.4</td>
                    <td valign="top" class="terms">Equipment&rdquo; shall mean all Equipment including any accessories supplied on hire by the Company to the Customer (and where the context so permits shall include any supply of services). The Equipment shall be as described on the invoices, quotations, sales orders, order confirmations, tile enquiries, tile estimates, authority to hire, or any other work authorisations form provided by the Company to the Customer.</td>
                  </tr>
                  <tr>
                    <td valign="top" class="terms style1">1.5</td>
                    <td valign="top" class="terms">&ldquo;Goods&rdquo; shall mean Goods supplied by the Company to the Customer including but not limited to: ceramic tiles, porcelain tiles, natural stone tiles, mosaic tiles, glass tiles, adhesives, sealers and Goods incidental to installation of tiles (and where the context so permits shall include any supply of Services as hereinafter defined) and are as described on the invoices, quotations, sales orders, order confirmations, tile enquiries, tile estimates, work authorisations or any other forms as provided by the Company to the Customer.</td>
                  </tr>
                  <tr>
                    <td valign="top" class="terms style1">1.6</td>
                    <td valign="top" class="terms">&ldquo;Services&rdquo; shall mean all Services supplied by the Company to the Customer and includes any advice or recommendations (and where the context so permits shall include any supply of Goods as defined above).</td>
                  </tr>
                  <tr>
                    <td valign="top" class="terms style1">1.7</td>
                    <td valign="top" class="terms">&ldquo;Price&rdquo; shall mean the Price payable for the Goods as agreed between the Company and the Customer in accordance with clause  of this contract.</td>
                  </tr>
                  <tr>
                    <td valign="top" class="terms style1">&nbsp;</td>
                    <td valign="top" class="terms">&nbsp;</td>
                  </tr>
                  <tr>
                    <td valign="top" class="terms style1">2.</td>
                    <td valign="top" class="terms" style="font-size:12px;color:#666666;"><strong>The Commonwealth Trade Practices Act 1974 (&ldquo;TPA&rdquo;) and Fair Trading Acts (&ldquo;FTA&rdquo;)</strong></td>
                  </tr>
                  <tr>
                    <td valign="top" class="terms style1">2.1</td>
                    <td valign="top" class="terms">Nothing in this agreement is intended to have the effect of contracting out of any applicable provisions of the TPA or the FTA in each of the States and Territories of Australia, except to the extent permitted by those Acts where applicable.</td>
                  </tr>
                  <tr>
                    <td valign="top" class="terms style1">&nbsp;</td>
                    <td valign="top" class="terms">&nbsp;</td>
                  </tr>
                  <tr>
                    <td valign="top" class="terms style1">3.</td>
                    <td valign="top" class="terms" style="font-size:12px;color:#666666;"><strong>Acceptance</strong></td>
                  </tr>
                  <tr>
                    <td valign="top" class="terms style1">3.1</td>
                    <td valign="top" class="terms">Any instructions received by the Company from the Customer for the supply of Goods and/or the Customer&rsquo;s acceptance of Goods supplied by the Company shall constitute acceptance of the terms and conditions contained herein.</td>
                  </tr>
                  <tr>
                    <td valign="top" class="terms style1">3.2</td>
                    <td valign="top" class="terms">The Customer acknowledges and agrees that Prices quoted are structured on a per piece basis and where applicable a covered square metre price is given to take into account industry accepted norms for jointing requirements.</td>
                  </tr>
                  <tr>
                    <td valign="top" class="terms style1">3.3</td>
                    <td valign="top" class="terms">Where the Company gives advice, recommendations, information, assistance or service to the Customer or the Customers agent, regarding the Goods or Services then it is given in good faith and the Company shall not be liable in any way whatsoever for any damages, losses or costs however arising resulting from the Customer relying on the same.</td>
                  </tr>
                  <tr>
                    <td valign="top" class="terms style1">3.4</td>
                    <td valign="top" class="terms">Where more than one Customer has entered into this agreement, the Customers shall be jointly and severally liable for all payments of the Price.</td>
                  </tr>
                  <tr>
                    <td valign="top" class="terms style1">3.5</td>
                    <td valign="top" class="terms">Upon acceptance of these terms and conditions by the Customer the terms and conditions are binding and can only be amended with the written consent of the Company.</td>
                  </tr>
                  <tr>
                    <td valign="top" class="terms style1">3.6</td>
                    <td valign="top" class="terms">Where the customer is a debtor of the Company, the Customer shall give the Company not less than fourteen (14) days prior written notice of any proposed change of ownership of the Customer or any change in the Customer&rsquo;s name and/or any other change in the Customer&rsquo;s details (including but not limited to: changes in the Customer&rsquo;s address, telephone number, facsimile number, e-mail address ABN Number, business practice, trading style or structure). Where the Customer has an approved credit facility with the Company, the Customer agrees to notify the Company of any pending legal action against the Customer by another creditor.  The Customer shall be liable for any loss incurred by the Company as a result of the Customer&rsquo;s failure to comply with this clause.</td>
                  </tr>
                  <tr>
                    <td valign="top" class="terms style1">3.7</td>
                    <td valign="top" class="terms">Goods are supplied by the Company only on the terms and conditions of trade herein to the exclusion of anything to the contrary in the terms of the Customer&rsquo;s order notwithstanding that any such order is placed on terms that purport to override these terms and conditions of trade and such alternate terms and conditions have been agreed to in writing in advance by the Company.</td>
                  </tr>
                  <tr>
                    <td valign="top" class="terms style1">&nbsp;</td>
                    <td valign="top" class="terms">&nbsp;</td>
                  </tr>
                  <tr>
                    <td valign="top" class="terms style1">4.</td>
                    <td valign="top" class="terms" style="font-size:12px;color:#666666;"><strong>Price and Payment</strong></td>
                  </tr>
                  <tr>
                    <td valign="top" class="terms style1">4.1</td>
                    <td valign="top" class="terms">At the Company&rsquo;s sole discretion the Price shall be either:</td>
                  </tr>
                  <tr>
                    <td valign="top" class="terms style1">&nbsp;</td>
                    <td valign="top" class="terms"><blockquote style="line-height:14px;padding-top:0;padding-bottom:0;margin-top:0;margin-bottom:0;">(a)as indicated on invoices, sales orders, order confirmations (all of which are always issued on an E&amp;OE basis) provided by the Company to the Customer in respect of Goods supplied; or<br />
                        (b)the Company&rsquo;s current price at the date of delivery of the Goods according to the Company&rsquo;s current Price lists (which are always issued on an E&amp;OE basis); or<br />
                        (c)the Company&rsquo;s quoted Price (subject to clause 4.3) which shall be binding upon the Company provided that the Customer shall accept the Company&rsquo;s quotation in writing within thirty (30) days.</blockquote></td>
                  </tr>
                  <tr>
                    <td valign="top" class="terms style1">4.2</td>
                    <td valign="top" class="terms">All price lists are are issued on an E&amp;OE basis, supersede all previous price lists which have an earlier issue date, are subject to change without notice, and are not to be construed as an offer.  Any item not included on a price list should be considered unavailable/deleted/discontinued.</td>
                  </tr>
                  <tr>
                    <td valign="top" class="terms style1">4.3</td>
                    <td valign="top" class="terms">The Company reserves the right to change the Price in the event of a variation to the Company&rsquo;s quotation. Any variation from the plan of scheduled works or specifications (including, but not limited to, any variation due to unforeseen circumstances, or as a result of fluctuations in the currency exchange rate, government charges, or due to ocean freight charges being incurred, or as a result of increases to the Company in the cost of finished goods, materials and labour) will be charged for on the basis of the Company&rsquo;s quotation and will be shown as variations on the invoice.  Payment for all variations must be made in full at their time of completion.</td>
                  </tr>
                  <tr>
                    <td valign="top" class="terms style1">4.4</td>
                    <td valign="top" class="terms">At the Company&rsquo;s sole discretion a non-refundable deposit may be required for an order to be confirmed.</td>
                  </tr>
                  <tr>
                    <td valign="top" class="terms style1">4.5</td>
                    <td valign="top" class="terms">At the Company&rsquo;s sole discretion:</td>
                  </tr>
                  <tr>
                    <td valign="top" class="terms style1">&nbsp;</td>
                    <td valign="top" class="terms"><blockquote style="line-height:14px;padding-top:0;padding-bottom:0;margin-top:0;margin-bottom:0;">(a)payment shall be due before delivery of the Goods.<br />
                        (b)payment for approved account holder&rsquo;s shall be due thirty (30) days following the end of the month in which a statement/invoice is posted, faxed or e-mailed to the Customer&rsquo;s address or address for notices (Eg October purchases are payable on/before 30 November).</blockquote></td>
                  </tr>
                  <tr>
                    <td valign="top" class="terms style1">4.6</td>
                    <td valign="top" class="terms">Time for payment for the Goods shall be of the essence and will be stated on the invoice or any other forms. If no time is stated then payment shall be due before delivery of the Goods.</td>
                  </tr>
                  <tr>
                    <td valign="top" class="terms style1">4.7</td>
                    <td valign="top" class="terms">Payment will be made by cash, or by cheque, or by bank cheque, or by credit card (plus a surcharge of up to two and a half percent (2.5%) of the Price), or by direct credit, or by any other method as agreed to between the Customer and the Company.</td>
                  </tr>
                  <tr>
                    <td valign="top" class="terms style1">4.8</td>
                    <td valign="top" class="terms">GST and other taxes and duties that may be applicable shall be added to the Price except when they are expressly included in the Price.</td>
                  </tr>
                  <tr>
                    <td valign="top" class="terms style1">&nbsp;</td>
                    <td valign="top" class="terms">&nbsp;</td>
                  </tr>
                  <tr>
                    <td valign="top" class="terms style1">5.</td>
                    <td valign="top" class="terms" style="font-size:12px;color:#666666;"><strong>Delivery of Goods</strong></td>
                  </tr>
                  <tr>
                    <td valign="top" class="terms style1">5.1</td>
                    <td valign="top" class="terms">All goods unless specifically noted are sold &ldquo;ex store&rdquo; on a &ldquo;freight forward&rdquo; basis and are transported at the Customer&rsquo;s risk and expense.  The Customer is responsible for arranging their own insurance for the Goods. The Company&rsquo;s responsibility for damage to or shortage in the goods ceases upon despatch or pickup from our premises.</td>
                  </tr>
                  <tr>
                    <td valign="top" class="terms style1">5.2</td>
                    <td valign="top" class="terms">The Company reserves the right to subcontract commercial carriers to deliver goods on the Customer&rsquo;s behalf and at the Customer&rsquo;s risk.</td>
                  </tr>
                  <tr>
                    <td valign="top" class="terms style1">5.3</td>
                    <td valign="top" class="terms">At the Company&rsquo;s sole discretion, delivery of the Goods shall take place when the Customer takes possession of the Goods at the Customer&rsquo;s nominated address (in the event that the Goods are delivered by the Company or the Company&rsquo;s nominated carrier).</td>
                  </tr>
                  <tr>
                    <td valign="top" class="terms style1">5.4</td>
                    <td valign="top" class="terms">At the Company&rsquo;s sole discretion the costs of delivery are:</td>
                  </tr>
                  <tr>
                    <td valign="top" class="terms style1">&nbsp;</td>
                    <td valign="top" class="terms"><blockquote style="line-height:14px;padding-top:0;padding-bottom:0;margin-top:0;margin-bottom:0;">(a)in addition to the Price; or<br />
                        (b)for the Customer&rsquo;s account.</blockquote></td>
                  </tr>
                  <tr>
                    <td valign="top" class="terms style1">5.5</td>
                    <td valign="top" class="terms">The Customer shall make all arrangements necessary to take delivery of the Goods whenever they are tendered for delivery. In the event that the Customer is unable to take delivery of the Goods as arranged then the Company shall be entitled to charge a reasonable fee for redelivery.</td>
                  </tr>
                  <tr>
                    <td valign="top" class="terms style1">5.6</td>
                    <td valign="top" class="terms">Delivery of the Goods to a third party nominated by the Customer is deemed to be delivery to the Customer for the purposes of this agreement.</td>
                  </tr>
                  <tr>
                    <td valign="top" class="terms style1">5.7</td>
                    <td valign="top" class="terms">The Company may deliver the Goods by separate instalments. Each separate instalment shall be invoiced and paid in accordance with the provisions in these terms and conditions.</td>
                  </tr>
                  <tr>
                    <td valign="top" class="terms style1">5.8</td>
                    <td valign="top" class="terms">The failure of the Company to deliver shall not entitle either party to treat this contract as repudiated.</td>
                  </tr>
                  <tr>
                    <td valign="top" class="terms style1">5.9</td>
                    <td valign="top" class="terms">The Company shall not be liable for any loss or damage whatsoever due to failure by the Company to deliver the Goods (or any of them) promptly or at all, where due to circumstances beyond the control of the Company.</td>
                  </tr>
                  <tr>
                    <td valign="top" class="terms style1">5.10</td>
                    <td valign="top" class="terms">The delivery records of the Company shall be prima facie proof of delivery of the Goods to the Customer of the quantity and description stated therein, in good order &amp; condition, and the Customer&rsquo;s receipt thereof in the same condition.</td>
                  </tr>
                  <tr>
                    <td valign="top" class="terms style1">&nbsp;</td>
                    <td valign="top" class="terms">&nbsp;</td>
                  </tr>
                  <tr>
                    <td valign="top" class="terms style1">6.</td>
                    <td valign="top" class="terms" style="font-size:12px;color:#666666;"><strong>Risk</strong></td>
                  </tr>
                  <tr>
                    <td valign="top" class="terms style1">6.1</td>
                    <td valign="top" class="terms">If the Company retains ownership of the Goods nonetheless, all risk for the Goods passes to the Customer on delivery.</td>
                  </tr>
                  <tr>
                    <td valign="top" class="terms style1">6.2</td>
                    <td valign="top" class="terms">If any of the Goods are damaged or destroyed following delivery but prior to ownership passing to the Customer, the Company is entitled to receive all insurance proceeds payable for the Goods. The production of these terms and conditions by the Company is sufficient evidence of the Company&rsquo;s rights to receive the insurance proceeds without the need for any person dealing with the Company to make further enquiries.</td>
                  </tr>
                  <tr>
                    <td valign="top" class="terms style1">6.3</td>
                    <td valign="top" class="terms">Where the Customer expressly requests the Company to leave Goods outside the Company&rsquo;s premises for collection or to deliver the Goods to an unattended location then such Goods shall be left at the Customer&rsquo;s sole risk and it shall be the Customer&rsquo;s responsibility to ensure the Goods are insured adequately or at all.</td>
                  </tr>
                  <tr>
                    <td valign="top" class="terms style1">6.4</td>
                    <td valign="top" class="terms">Where the Company gives advice, recommendations, information, assistance or service to the Customer or the Customers agent, regarding the suitability or purpose of the Goods or Services then it is given in good faith and the Company shall not be liable in any way whatsoever for any damages, losses or costs however arising resulting from the Customer relying on the same.</td>
                  </tr>
                  <tr>
                    <td valign="top" class="terms style1">6.5</td>
                    <td valign="top" class="terms">If delivery is delayed as a consequence of the Customer&rsquo;s instructions, or lack thereof, then the Company may at is sole discretion, store the Goods for the Customer at the Customer&rsquo;s risk, and the Customer shall be liable for all storage costs charged or incurred by the Company and in the event that the Goods are stored elsewhere all cartage charges incurred by the Company.</td>
                  </tr>
                  <tr>
                    <td valign="top" class="terms style1">6.6</td>
                    <td valign="top" class="terms">The Customer acknowledges and agrees that pallet, container and indent Prices, where given, are not to be construed as quotations and the Company reserves the right to withdraw or vary such Prices.</td>
                  </tr>
                  <tr>
                    <td valign="top" class="terms style1">6.7</td>
                    <td valign="top" class="terms">Samples of Goods are supplied as a guide only.</td>
                  </tr>
                  <tr>
                    <td valign="top" class="terms style1">6.8</td>
                    <td valign="top" class="terms">The Customer acknowledges that Goods supplied may exhibit variations in shade, colour, durability, texture, size, weight, dimensions, surface and finish, and may fade or change colour over time. The Company will make every effort to match batches of product supplied, or to match batches of product to sales samples, catalogues, marketing literature or website images in order to minimise such variations but shall not be liable in any way whatsoever where such variations occur.</td>
                  </tr>
                  <tr>
                    <td valign="top" class="terms style1">6.9</td>
                    <td valign="top" class="terms">The customer acknowledges that shade &amp; size variation is inherent in all kiln-fired products including ceramic, glass, porcelain &amp; terracotta tiles and may be evident between shipments of a particular Good or even among Goods of one type from the same shipment.</td>
                  </tr>
                  <tr>
                    <td valign="top" class="terms style1">6.10</td>
                    <td valign="top" class="terms">The customer acknowledges that ceramic glazes are not guaranteed against crazing.</td>
                  </tr>
                  <tr>
                    <td valign="top" class="terms style1">6.11</td>
                    <td valign="top" class="terms">The customer acknowledges that all Goods made from natural products including but not limited to: terracotta, wood, stone, slate, marble, sandstone &amp; granite are sold on the basis that they are man-manipulated but not man-made and are therefore sold with no guarantee or warranty whatsoever.  Such Goods may exhibit significant variations in colour, physical dimensions, density, surface texture, slip-resistance &amp; markings/veining/pattern from one piece to the next.</td>
                  </tr>
                  <tr>
                    <td valign="top" class="terms style1">6.12</td>
                    <td valign="top" class="terms">The customer acknowledges that any Goods produced through polishing, grinding or honing processes may, with varying light sources and at differing angles, display optical effects such as hazing or smudging as an inherent characteristic.  These are visual effects only and do not affect the performance or life span of the Goods and is not considered a defect by the relevant Australian standard.</td>
                  </tr>
                  <tr>
                    <td valign="top" class="terms style1">6.13</td>
                    <td valign="top" class="terms">The customer acknowledges that all natural stone, terracotta &amp; other porous tiles &amp; Goods may be subject to salt attack and must be kept properly sealed at all times -- including any bullnosed or exposed edges.  As a rule-of-thumb, when water no longer &ldquo;beads&rdquo; on the surface of porous tiles &amp; Goods, they then require re-sealing.  Porous tiles &amp; Goods must have an effective, working sealer barrier present at all times to be properly sealed and inhibit salt infiltration.</td>
                  </tr>
                  <tr>
                    <td valign="top" class="terms style1">6.14</td>
                    <td valign="top" class="terms">The Customer acknowledges and agrees that the Company recommends that immediately after installing or applying the Goods, suitable protective measures be taken to avoid unnecessary damage to the Goods.  The Company shall not be held liable for any loss, damages, or costs however resulting from tiles and other Goods becoming scratched by foreign abrasive material, stained or contaminated with foreign substances during or after installation or application.</td>
                  </tr>
                  <tr>
                    <td valign="top" class="terms style1">6.15</td>
                    <td valign="top" class="terms">The Company shall not be held liable for any loss, damages, or costs however resulting from any acids, chemical compounds, abrasives or solvents used in the cleaning or installation of any Goods.  This is irrespective or whether or not the cleaning is conducted by the Company, the Customer, or a third party.  Hydrochloric acid in particular, should never be used on the surface of any type of tile, natural stone or terracotta.</td>
                  </tr>
                  <tr>
                    <td valign="top" class="terms style1">6.16</td>
